  "text": "Notable improvements are made by Boneh and Durfee [CITATION_1] who heuristically but practically used the LLL algorithm for finding short vectors in lattices to show that RSA is insecure whenever d < N 1− 1 √ 2 . However, they conjecture that RSA is insecure if d < N 1/2 apart from an espilon.",
